arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics shipment tracker. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/` with Interactive Auto, Global mode and Individual authentication.

**Project structure:**
- Server project: `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/`
- Client project: `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/`

**Requirements:**
1. Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
2. Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
3. Every page involves interactive controls
4. Staff and customers authenticate with individual accounts (already scaffolded)

**Architecture rules (Auto Global mode):**
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- No direct DB access from interactive components — use HTTP APIs
- Define interfaces in `.Client` project, implement with HttpClient there
- On server, implement the same interface with direct DB/EF access
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Expose data via minimal API endpoints on the server

**Tasks to complete:**

### 1. Create the Shipment model (shared between projects)
Create `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed
}
```

### 2. Create the IShipmentService interface in the Client project
Create `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string customerEmail);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
}
```

### 3. Create the HttpClient-based implementation in the Client project
Create `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient httpClient) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<Shipment?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string customerEmail)
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>($"api/shipments/customer/{Uri.EscapeDataString(customerEmail)}") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        await httpClient.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
    }
}
```

### 4. Create the server-side implementation using EF Core
Create `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext dbContext) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await dbContext.Shipments.OrderByDescending(s => s.ShippedDate).ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await dbContext.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string customerEmail)
    {
        return await dbContext.Shipments
            .Where(s => s.CustomerEmail == customerEmail)
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.ShippedDate)
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var shipment = await dbContext.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment is not null)
        {
            shipment.Status = status;
            await dbContext.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }
}
```

### 5. Add DbSet to ApplicationDbContext
Edit `/tmp/sv-e08c791593e44eee8bcbb2693653da51/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class ApplicationDbContext(DbContextOptions<ApplicationDbContext> options) : IdentityDbContext<ApplicationUser>(options)
{
    public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
}
```

### 6. Update Server Program.cs
Add these registrations BEFORE `var app = builder.Build();`:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```
Add the necessary `using` statements at the top:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Services;
```

Add API endpoints AFTER `app.UseAntiforgery();` and BEFORE `app.MapStaticAssets();`:
```csharp
app.MapGet("/api/shipments", async (IShipmentService service) =>
    await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync()).RequireAuthorization();

app.MapGet("/api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    var shipment = await service.GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber);
    return shipment is not null ? Results.Ok(shipment) : Results.NotFound();
}).RequireAuthorization();

app.MapGet("/api/shipments/customer/{customerEmail}", async (string customerEmail, IShipmentService service) =>
    await service.GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(customerEmail)).RequireAuthorization();

app.MapPut("/api/shipments/{id}/status", async (int id, ShipmentStatus status, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    await service.UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(id, status);
    return Results.NoContent();
}).RequireAuthorization();
```
Add `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;` at the top too.

### 7. Update Client Program.cs
Add HttpClient and service registration:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddHttpClient("ShipmentTracker.ServerAPI", client =>
    client.BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress));
